    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Exercise 3\n",
        "\n",
        "Calculate the determinant of the matrix $C$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$C = \\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 3 & 1 & 4 \\\\ 1 & 0 & 0 & 6 \\\\ 3 & 2 & 1 & 5 \\\\ 2 & 1 & 4 & 0 \\end{bmatrix}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "In this case, we will calculate the determinant by expanding the matrix over the second row:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\det C = (-1)^{2+1}\\cdot1\\cdot \\det \\begin{bmatrix} 3 & 1 & 4 \\\\ 2 & 1 & 5 \\\\ 1 & 4 & 0 \\end{bmatrix} + (-1)^{2+4}\\cdot 6\\cdot \\det \\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 3 & 1 \\\\ 3 & 2 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 1 & 4 \\end{bmatrix}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\det \\begin{bmatrix} 3 & 1 & 4 \\\\ 2 & 1 & 5 \\\\ 1 & 4 & 0 \\end{bmatrix} = +1 \\cdot \\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 4 \\\\ 1 & 5 \\end{bmatrix} - 4 \\cdot \\begin{bmatrix} 3 & 4 \\\\ 2 & 5 \\end{bmatrix} = 1 - 4(15 - 8) = 1 - 28 = -27$$\n",
        "\n",
        "and\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\det \\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 3 & 1 \\\\ 3 & 2 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 1 & 4 \\end{bmatrix} = +1 \\cdot \\det \\begin{bmatrix} 3 & 2 \\\\ 2 & 1\\end{bmatrix} - 1 \\cdot \\det \\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 3 \\\\ 2 & 1 \\end{bmatrix} + 4 \\cdot \\det \\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 3 \\\\ 3 & 2\\end{bmatrix} = +1\\cdot(3 - 4) - 1\\cdot(2 - 6) + 4\\cdot(4 - 9) = (-1) - (2 - 6) + 4(4 - 9) = (-1) - (-4) + 4(-5) = -1 + 4 - 20 = -17$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore, substituting the results, we get: $$\\det C = -1 \\cdot (-27) + 6 \\cdot (-17) = -75$$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4KfcSakP9Cr1"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import sympy as sp\n",
        "\n",
        "C=sp.Matrix([\n",
        "\t\t\t [2, 3, 1, 4],\n",
        "\t\t\t [1, 0, 0, 6],\n",
        "\t\t\t [3, 2, 1, 5],\n",
        "\t\t\t [2, 1, 4, 0]\n",
        "\t\t\t ])\n",
        "C.det()"
